summary: This is a travel authorization notification for a DOJ trip related to the Epstein investigation, specifically for a witness interview in Pensacola, FL scheduled for February 19-20, 2020. The authorization was approved by one official and is pending further approval.

events.title: Planned Witness Interview in Pensacola
events.description: A witness interview related to the Epstein investigation was scheduled to take place in Pensacola, FL.

keyFacts: A travel authorization (ID 11062816) was approved on February 14, 2020, for a DOJ trip related to the Epstein investigation.
The purpose of the trip was a witness interview under the case reference 'R20NYS13401 - Epstein Investigation'.
The travel was scheduled for February 19-20, 2020, to Pensacola, FL.
The authorization status was 'Pending Authorization Approval', indicating it required further sign-off.
The document confirms ongoing investigative activity in the Epstein case as of early 2020.
